Subject: Re: networks and addresses 
Date: Sat, 29 Mar 86 14:09:44 PST

Hear, hear!  I would love to have as many as possible of the magic numbers
handled by the name servers.  4.2BSD provided similar interfaces
for looking up hosts, networks, protocol numbers, and port numbers.
The first of these is now implemented by a name server, but the others
still look through text files stored on each host.  Of course,
the file of network names and numbers is still generated from the NIC
host table.

		Mike
